<!-- About DIGINFO, 22 Years of Pioneering Philippine IT R&D and Engineering -->
<p>The Philippine IT industry is not a big one. And within this small community, just a few Filipino-owned companies do R&D for their own branded products that ferociously compete with those from global technology behemoths such as Microsoft, SAP, IBM and Oracle which are being marketed by their local sales offices.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>From this very few Filipino IT engineering companies, only a few had been in the business for more than 10 years, and possibly less than five had existed for 20 years or more.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>DIGINFO is one of these few quite lucky companies that had survived, persisted and thrived in the past 20 years.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Founded on January 6, 1992 by Nilo Poso, an SGV and UP TMC alumnus, DIGINFO has crafted and evolved DIGINFO iTechnology, a homegrown infostructure system, which consists of iMACHINE, BOS/e, iBOS/e and mBOS/e platforms and their respective suites of business applications.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>DIGINFO's first product -- PayFast, a Philippine payroll software released in 1993 -- is still being used by several companies such as Wendy's and Aristocrat Restaurant. The same goes for DIGINFO's second product -- PeopleWARE, a Philippine payroll and HR software -- which still runs in Rustan's. Such long usage tells about the longevity of DIGINFO technologies in delivering value and long-term benefits.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<b>Awards & Citations</b>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>CITEM has adjudged DIGINFO's iBOS/e WebShell and mBOS/e SMS Server as the best e-business software and best mobile software, respectively, during its e-Commerce event in 2005. In 2008, UP Diliman's Prof. Elvira Zamora has featured DIGINFO as one of the innovative Philippine companies that harness and manage technology to their advantage in her paper presented at the Asian Productivity Office (APO) technology management conference in South Korea.</p>
